&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;a6&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td&gt;… the happiness of joy comes about in his body: he is not able to tell the joy of the fulfilling of the dear [lit. great] wish, to teach it or to let it know in a metaphor.&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td&gt;667&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;b3&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td&gt;Who has the &lt;i&gt;jñānasaṃbhāra &lt;/i&gt;of a hundred kalpas here, …&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td&gt;675&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;b4&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td&gt;If his definite shape and form are not gone or lost, the Āryamarga [the noble path] is at once lit up for him without teacher and without teaching.&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td&gt;675&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;b5&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td&gt;… he witnesses the 37 laws and attains the rank of a &lt;i&gt;pratyeka &lt;/i&gt;Buddha and second he becomes worthy of receiving gifts …&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td&gt;675&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;b6-7&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td&gt;To whom, however, compassion and wisdom arise, and who does not turn back from the effort for countless ages, and does not make the consciousness of hindrance … and takes …, and does not think «I cannot», even &lt;i&gt;oṣ &lt;/i&gt;or honey does not delight his heart if he takes the sorrows of the beings of the five births in his &lt;i&gt;vajra&lt;/i&gt;-like heart.  (cf [[Adams, DoT]]: 476)&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td&gt;675&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;/p&gt;
